@h1 A version from Me-Turan


@(2.A.1 = 1-7) I will sing the song of the man of battle, the man of battle. I will sing the song of Lord @wDN{Gilgameš}, the man of battle, I will sing the song of the lord with the very black beard, the man of battle. I will sing the song of him with the well-proportioned limbs, the man of battle. I will sing the song of him in his prime (?), the man of battle. I will sing the song of him who batters the wicked, the man of battle. The king, the lord, having …… as his mother who bore him ……, wishing to wash (?) in the river.

@(2.A.8 = 8-18) My lord, having sought entry into the garden planted with junipers, the lord, coming from the @fsux{ŋipar}, sheared the wool of the fleecy sheep ……; …… he sat down ……. The king …… bending …… with the oar; the prince covered …… with the oar, as if it was of flourishing reed. You covered their wicked ones, as if ……, with water. He gave …… to his mother who bore him. In the wide courtyard ……, @wDN{Gilgameš} …….  ((1 line unclear))  In the great courtyard …….

@(2.A.19 = 19-21) Then …… the canopy ……. Holy @wDN{Inana} perceived the canopy, from the palace of the @fsux{abzu}, she perceived the canopy:

@(2.A.22 = 22-27) @q[Inana,Gilgamec]{“My wild bull, my man, I shall not let you ……! @wDN{Gilgameš}, I shall not let you ……! I shall not let you dispense justice in my @wTN{E-ana}! I shall not let you pronounce verdicts in my holy @fsux{ŋipar}! I shall not let you dispense justice in the @wTN{E-ana} beloved by @wDN{An}! @wDN{Gilgameš}, may you ……, may I …….”}

@(2.A.28 = 28-39) The king, …… his mouth, the king …… to his mother who bore him. @wDN{Gilgameš} …… to @wDN{Ninsumun} ……: @q[Gilgamec,Ninsumun]{“O mother who bore me, how ……! By the door of the great gate ……. From the crenellations of the wall ……: @q[Inana,Gilgamec]{“My wild bull, my man, I shall not let you go ……! @wDN{Gilgameš}, I shall not let you go ……! You dispensed justice in my @wTN{E-ana} -- I shall not let you go! You pronounced verdicts in my holy @fsux{ŋipar} -- I shall not let you go, in his beloved …… @wTN{E-ana}!"”}”}

@(2.A.40 = 40-41) When he had spoken thus to the mother who bore him, the mother who bore him replied to @wDN{Gilgameš}:

