@(2.D.5 = 5-9) @q[Gilgamec,Lugal-gabajar]{“My musician, @wPN{Lugal-gabaŋar}, perform your song, tune your strings! Give me beer to drink! Fill my bronze jug again! ……”} @wPN{Lugal-gabaŋar} replied to his master, @wDN{Gilgameš}: @q[Gilgamec,Lugal-gabajar]{“My master, you may eat, and you may drink -- but as for me, how does this matter concern me?”}

@(2.D.10 = 10-15) To defeat the Bull, ……, @wDN{Gilgameš}, to defeat the Bull, ……. …… his harness of fifty @noteref{text: five-sixths} minas. …… his sword weighing seven talents and thirty minas. …… his battle axe. @q[Gilgamec,Ninsumun]{“My mother who bore me …….”}

@(2.D.16 = 16-23) His sister ……. His mother who bore him ……. @wDN{Peštur}, his little sister ……. @wDN{Gilgameš} …… @q[Gilgamec,others]{“My mother who bore me, in the house (?) of Enki (?) ……. @wDN{Peštur}, the little sister, ……, will bring back the cattle to their tethering stakes ……, will bring back the sheep to their tethering stakes …….”}

@(2.D.24 = 24-32) @q[Gilgamec,Bull of Heaven]{“Bull of Heaven, you -- you, ……, yes, you! You crush them ……, and I crush them ……. If you crush them, …… They shall consign your hide to the streets ……. They shall consign your intestines to the broad square ……. The widows' sons of my city shall each take their share of your meat in baskets. They shall consign your carcass to the knacker's, and I shall turn your two horns into flasks for pouring fine oil to @wDN{Inana} in @wTN{E-ana}.”}

@(2.D.33 = 33-38) The Bull …… in the dust. @wDN{Gilgameš} …… and @wPN{Enkidu} ……. Their fellow-citizens ……. …… with dust, like a young calf unused to the yoke. @wPN{Enkidu} stood by (?) the Bull's head and spoke to @wDN{Gilgameš}:

@(2.D.39 = 39-44) @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“Ho, magnificent one, extending your staff of office, born of noble lineage, splendour of the gods, furious-hearted bull, standing ready for battle, warrior, …… your hand ……! The people ……, the people …….”}

@(2.D.45 = 45-48) When @wPN{Enkidu} had spoken thus to @wDN{Gilgameš}, @wDN{Gilgameš} himself smote its skull with his axe weighing seven talents. The Bull reared up so high, so high that it overbalanced. It spattered like rain, it spread itself out like the harvested crop.

@(2.D.49 = 49-52) The king took his knife in his hand, just as if he were a master chef. He hit @wDN{Inana} with a haunch, he made her flee away like a pigeon, and demolished those ramparts. Standing by (?) the Bull's head, the king wept bitter tears: @q[Gilgamec,Bull of Heaven]{“Just as I can destroy you, so shall I do the same to her (?).”}

@(2.D.53 = 53-59) As he spoke, he consigned its hide to the streets, he consigned its intestines to the broad square, and the widows' sons of his city each took their share of its meat in baskets. He consigned its carcass to the knacker's, and turned its two horns into flasks for pouring fine oil to @wDN{Inana} in @wTN{E-ana}. For the death of the Bull of Heaven: holy @wDN{Inana}, it is sweet to praise you!



